#### Improvements for Developers
- Developers no longer need to perform manual steps to enable TLS connections to their service instances.
- Developers can see metrics for their service instances via the [CF CLI Log Cache plugin](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/log-cache-cli).

#### Improvements for Operators
- Operators can run the `find-deprecated-bindings` BOSH errand to discover service instances with outdated service bindings and service keys. For more information, see [MySQL for PCF Errands](errands.html#find-deprecated-bindings).
- Operators can configure up to nine service plans in the tile.
- Operators can mark service plans as **free** or **paid** so that developer can be aware of costs associated with certain service plans.
- Operators can configure the default idle timeout for connections to a service instance to allow compliance with CIS security benchmarks.


